Date: 3 Nov 94 11:25:52 CST
Organization: Western Kentucky University, Bowling Green, KY

I just wanted to tell all of you to exhibit caution if you plan on
buying a system from Zenon Technologies.  They advertise in Computer
Shopper and other magazines.  They emphasize there great customer
service & tech. support.

A few weeks ago, a friend of mine purchased a $2600 486DX2/66 system
from Zenon (MPCII, VideoForge, 15" mon., 8 Mb RAM...).  Right out of
the box, the monitor (CTX) was extremely blurry.  Text can be read
near the center of the screen, but was unreadable anywhere near the
edges.  He immediately call Zenon, who asked him if it was okay to
charge his credit card when a new monitor is sent and credit his card
when the defective monitor arrives.  He said he would get back with
tech. support in a few days.  My friend tried playing the CD games
that came with the system... not a single one work.  I had to come
over and re-install the games, mess around with his CONFIG.SYS and
AUTOEXEC.BAT to get most of them to work.  1 game even requires a
different set-up, so I had to use multi.-configs. in the config &
auto.  That really wasn't _TOO_ bad...

My friend decided (approx. 1 week after his computer arrived) that it
was not capable of doing what he wanted it to do.  His original plan
was to capture video via the VideoForge card that came with his
system and modify it (adding title, simple effects, etc.)  It should
also be noted that the saleperson he talked to told my friend that he
should have no problem doing this, even though he told the salesperson
he "doesn't know a thing about computers."  He called
Zenon (Zenon CLEARLY advertises a 30 day money-back guarantee) and
asked Zenon to take the computer back.  Zenon said they'll get back
with him.  They haven't yet (3 weeks have passed so far).  I called a
few days ago.  There tech. supp. line were busy, I left a message,
haven't heard from them since.  They're sale line (which is usually
not busy) tell me they cannot help me.

Anyways, my friend & I have tried to contact Zenon many times since
then.  I even left a message once stating that if I did not get a
response within 4 days, I would post a text file stating this
experience onto a computer newsgroup.  Apparently Zenon feels
unconcerned.  So my friend is stuck with $2600 worth of electronics
that he has no need for.  I wonder if this is the only incident of
this nature that anyone has had with this company...

My point is don't buy from ZENON.

