I bought a dx2/66, pci, multimedia, tape backup, 8 meg from Zenon
back in July and the system has performed without a hitch. I bought
an ADI Microscan 15" separately since i had read that ctx and mag were
average at best.

You definitely take a chance buying mailorder, especially from a lower
tier company like Zenon. (But even Micron, Gateway, etc have had their
share of troubles). Quantex seems to be right in the pricing "sweetspot"
right now - but i can't comment personally on their merchandise. 

Return policies may be better with the bigger companies, but you pay for
it. Getting thru to Zenon service can be hard - but play it smart, call
5 minutes before they are scheduled to "open" and keep trying. I've had
the best luck this way. Pay via credit card (esp Amex since you get extra
warranty coverage) so you can hold the charges in dispute if you don't
get what you paid for.

My only complaints about Zenon: the #9 video drivers were ancient (downloaded
new ones from #9), the sales people are even more abrupt after you've gotten
the goods (but time is literally money to these guys), the cabling is a bit
cluttered in front of the free simm slots (but they are still accessible).

Buy from the big boys if you think you'll need service. Take a chance (and save
$100's) if you are more techie (or at least have techie friends).   

