I would stick to the known systems or buy from people your friends recommend.
I ordered a 60 MHz Pentium from Zenon 6 months ago. It was a big mistake. For
instance, they had two cooling fans in the box per their advertising but the
second was just hanging by a single bolt thru a hole they drilled thru the
plastic! I would not have noticed this except the system would not boot up so
I opened the system....the SCSI cable wasn't even connected to the harddrive.
I was lucky. I was able to make them take back the system after arguing on
the phone. Zenon is also one of those companies that has their tech-line
constantly busy so you can't get help.

The moral of the story: Don't get sucked in by slick adds in Computer
Shopper like Zenon's. Also open your system when you get it so you know
that you got what you ordered. 

Hope that helps

